Q: how to use Service,ServiceLocator,portType,porttypeProxy and stub to create a java client A: <p>Create a client for the given wsdl and try this:</p>

<pre><code>WebServiceSoapBindingStub stub = new WebServiceSoapBindingStub();
stub._setProperty(Stub.ENDPOINT_ADDRESS_PROPERTY, wsdlUrl); 
WebService service = (WebService) stub;
service.authenticateUser(username,password); //service.yourservicename
</code></pre>

